 Ikechukwu Nnochir – Abuja A High Court of the Federal Capital Territory sitting in Apo, on Friday, remanded a former Director, of Legal Services,  Ministry of Petroleum Resources, Mrs. Grace Taiga, in prison over the alleged role she played in the activities that resulted in the controversial $9.6billion Process and Industrial Developments Limited  (P&ID) judgment debt. Justice Olukayode Adeniyi ordered that the defendant be taken to Suleja Prison in Niger State after she pleaded not guilty to an eight-count charge the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, (EFCC,) preferred against her. Continue reading P&ID $9.6bn liability: Court remands ex-Director in prison at Vanguard News. Source: Vanguard